libmobi
------------------------------------------
C library for handling Kindle (MOBI) formats of ebook documents

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libminiz2-2.2.0-1bl1
  libmobi-devel-0.11-1bl1
  libmobi0-0.11-1bl1
  libxml2-2.9.12-2
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.35.2-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libminiz-devel-2.2.0-1bl1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.12-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/bfabiszewski/libmobi

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/bfabiszewski/libmobi/archive/refs/tags/v0.11.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libmobi-0.11-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libmobi-0.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmobi-0.11-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmobi-0.11-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmobi0-0.11-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmobi-devel-0.11-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libmobi)
  /usr/bin/mobidrm.exe
  /usr/bin/mobimeta.exe
  /usr/bin/mobitool.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libmobi.README
  /usr/share/doc/libmobi/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libmobi/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libmobi/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/mobidrm.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/mobimeta.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/mobitool.1.gz

(libmobi0)
  /usr/bin/cygmobi-0.dll

(libmobi-devel)
  /usr/include/mobi.h
  /usr/lib/libmobi.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libmobi.pc

